    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i test drive it i get this really high pitched squealing noise when i hit the brakes. not sure if its a worn sensor or if i messed up the caliper or something. what should i check first?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Squealing brakes, right after a job like that, is a common nuisance. You should check the brake pads and rotors first, even if you just replaced them, because sometimes the new parts aren't seating quite right, or maybe a piece of old grime is still clinging to something. It's often a simple thing, like a tiny piece of grit stuck between the pad and the rotor, making a high-pitched whine. A good, solid check is to inspect the caliper hardware—make sure everything is clean and lubricated.",
