    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the pads and they look fine, and the rotors seem okay too. the sound is really piercing though, almost like a screeching sound that only happens right when the pressure is applied. could it be a hardware issue like the caliper pins being stuck, or is there something else that would make that specific sound?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A piercing screech, only when pressure is applied, sounds like something a little more aggressive than just a simple pad-to-rotor rub. That's where the hardware comes in, and you're right to suspect the caliper pins. If those pins are sticky, the caliper won't move freely, and that friction can create a nasty, high-pitched shriek. It's a very common gremlin in the system, usually caused by old grease hardening up or some dried-out corrosion. You'll want to grab your penetrating oil and give those pins a good, thorough cleaning and lubrication.",
      "source": "target",
